    "Management": {
      "text": "Treatment may be indicated in the following situations: severe/intractable headache, evidence of progressive decrease in visual acuity or visual field loss. Some ophthalmologists suggest treating all patients with papilledema.\nWeight loss\nAcetazolamide\n250mg QID (or 500mg BID) initially building up to 500-1000mg QID if tolerated. Use with caution in sulfa-allergic patients. (decreases CSF production)\nDiscontinue any causative medications\nShort course of systemic steroids, especially if any plans for surgical intervention\nRepeat\nLPs\n(decrease CSF pressure) - large volume LPs on the order of 30-40 cc of CSF\nFurosemide\n20mg PO BID, give potassium supp as needed\nIf above treatments are unsuccessful, surgical treatments may be considered.\nCSF Shunt (ventriculoperitoneal or lumboperitoneal) is often effective if vision is threatened\nOptic nerve sheath fenestration",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Acetazolamide",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Acetazolamide"
        },
        {
          "text": "LPs",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/LP"
        },
        {
          "text": "Furosemide",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Furosemide"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "Admit for:\nSevere pain\nFocal findings\nVision changes\nOtherwise, discharge with ophtho follow up for formal visual field monitoring",
      "subsections": {},
